<br><br>
E-PlayCD 0.5.2<br>
By Rahsheen Porter - 1999
<p>
E-PlayCD was one of the first Enlightenment Epplets. It allows you
to control your CD-ROM drive to play CD's. I tried to design it in
such a way that it would not simply lock your drive like most 
programs do. E-PlayCD grabs the drive, sends the command, and then
lets it go. It has CDDB support, a pop-up tracklist, a scrolling label
showing current track info, and a volume
slider. Most of the buttons are pretty self-explanatory, so click
_NEXT(buttons) and I'll explain them.

<p><p>
Comments or suggestions? rahsheen@cc.gatech.edu.
</font>
